47 // Open a file. Return bool upon success.
48 bool MatlabFileReader::Open(const std::string& file_name) {
49  // Close any open file before opening a new file.
50  if (IsOpen()) Close();
51 
52  // Open the new file.
53  mat_fp_ = Mat_Open(file_name.c_str(), MAT_ACC_RDONLY);
54  return IsOpen();
55 }
56 
57 // Read scalar. Returns bool indicating success.
58 bool MatlabFileReader::ReadScalar(const std::string& field_name,
59  double* value) {
60  if (!IsOpen()) return false;
61 
62  // Make sure 'value' is non-null.
63  if (!value) return false;
64 
65  // Extract this variable and check type.
66  matvar_t* variable = Mat_VarRead(mat_fp_, field_name.c_str());
67  if (!variable || variable->data_type != MAT_T_DOUBLE) return false;
68 
69  *value = *static_cast<double*>(variable->data);
70 
71  // Free variable.
72  Mat_VarFree(variable);
73  return true;
74 }
75 
76 // Read string. Returns bool indicating success.
77 bool MatlabFileReader::ReadString(const std::string& field_name,
78  std::string* value) {
79  if (!IsOpen()) return false;
80 
81  // Make sure 'value' is non-null.
82  if (!value) return false;
83 
84  // Extract this variable and check type.
85  matvar_t* variable = Mat_VarRead(mat_fp_, field_name.c_str());
86  if (!variable) return false; // || variable->data_type != MAT_T_UTF8) return false;
87 
88  value->assign(static_cast<char*>(variable->data));
89 
90  // Free variable.
91  Mat_VarFree(variable);
92  return true;
93 }

114 // Read vector. Returns bool indicating success.
115 bool MatlabFileReader::ReadVector(const std::string& field_name,
116  std::vector<double>* values) {
117  if (!IsOpen()) return false;
118 
119  // Make sure 'values' is non-null.
120  if (!values) return false;
121  values->clear();
122 
123  // Extract variable and check type.
124  matvar_t* variable = Mat_VarRead(mat_fp_, field_name.c_str());
125  if (!variable || variable->data_type != MAT_T_DOUBLE) return false;
126 
127  size_t num_elements = variable->nbytes / variable->data_size;
128  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < num_elements; ii++)
129  values->emplace_back(static_cast<double*>(variable->data)[ii]);
130 
131  // Free variable.
132  Mat_VarFree(variable);
133  return true;
134 }
135
